<p>Welcome to RareRecords.net. We think our name speaks for itself; we specialize in <em>rare records and memorabilia</em>. <p>Our emphasis is on the unusual and <strong>rare records</strong>. If you’re looking for a stock copy of the first album from Boston, for example, you probably won’t find that here. You may, however, find a half speed mastered pressing, a white label promotional copy, or perhaps a high quality imported pressing of the album from Japan. Our stock of rare records is continually changing, and we add new items each week, so if you don’t see what you’re looking for today, we suggest that you come back in a few days and see what we may have in stock at that time. Rare records don’t exactly grow on trees, but we are constantly looking for the unusual item and we do what we can to keep our inventory interesting.</p>
